<dl id="n19069g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n19" href="#n19069g">N19 (VI.B.19)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n19all.htm#n19069g"> 69(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> compensation</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Instead of this picture, however, there appeared the material of the story which he had been told by his grandfather shortly before: the tree, the wolves, and the taillessness (in the over-<mark>compensated</mark> form of the bushy tails of the alleged wolves). <small> Sigmund Freud, <a name="SFWM2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SFWM2"><cite title="source">&ldquo;From the History of an Infantile Neurosis (The &lsquo;Wolf Man&rsquo;)&rdquo;</cite></a> (1925) 513</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: The wolf man actually suffered (as a young adult) from acute constipation. Dr Freud&apos;s treatment of this condition led him to believe - and we cannot doubt the good doctor&apos;s sincerity - that he suffered rather from a complex desire both to be and anally to fuck and be fucked by both his mother and his father, a neurosis germinated in him by his seeing at the tender age <i>of one and a half years of age</i> a copulation scene between them, thrice repeated and <i>per anum</i>.</mm> </dd></dl>
